-- 4. VWAP
('vwap-pattern-confirmation',
'VWAP: Institutional Confirmation for Pattern Entries',
'Use VWAP as an institutional-grade confirmation filter for chart pattern entries during intraday sessions.',
E'## Why VWAP Matters for Pattern Traders\n\nVWAP (Volume Weighted Average Price) represents institutional fair value. When a chart pattern breakout occurs relative to VWAP, it tells you whether institutions are likely supporting or opposing the move.\n\n## How VWAP Confirms Patterns\n\n### Pattern Breakout Above VWAP = Institutional Support\n\nWhen a bullish pattern breakout occurs above VWAP, institutions are likely buying:\n\n- **Bull Flag breakout above VWAP** = Very strong confirmation\n- **Double Bottom neckline break above VWAP** = Institutions confirming reversal\n- **Triangle breakout above VWAP** = Smart money aligned\n\n### Pattern Breakdown Below VWAP = Institutional Distribution\n\nWhen a bearish pattern triggers below VWAP, institutions are likely selling:\n\n- **Bear Flag breakdown below VWAP** = Institutions confirming continuation\n- **Head & Shoulders neckline break below VWAP** = Smart money aligned\n\n### VWAP as Dynamic Support/Resistance for Patterns\n\n- VWAP often acts as the neckline or support/resistance within patterns\n- Patterns that form WITH VWAP as structural support/resistance are higher quality\n\n## VWAP Formula & Structure\n\nVWAP = Σ(Price × Volume) / Σ(Volume)\n\n- Resets each trading session\n- Becomes more stable as the day progresses\n- Standard deviation bands (±1σ, ±2σ) create trading zones\n\n## Best Times for VWAP + Pattern Trades\n\n- **10:00-11:30 AM:** VWAP stabilized, best pattern setups\n- **2:00-3:30 PM:** Volume returns, pattern breakouts with VWAP confirmation\n- **Avoid first 30 min:** VWAP too volatile for reliable confirmation\n\n## Risk Management\n\n- **Position Size:** 1% account risk on intraday pattern trades\n- **Stop Loss:** Pattern-based stops, not VWAP-based\n- **Risk-Reward:** 1.5:1 minimum for intraday\n- **Note:** VWAP resets daily — only use for intraday patterns\n\n## Common Mistakes\n\n- Using VWAP for swing/position pattern trades (it resets daily)\n- Trading patterns against VWAP direction\n- Ignoring VWAP context during pattern breakouts\n- Trading VWAP alone without pattern structure\n\n## Key Takeaway\n\nVWAP tells you where institutions consider "fair value." Pattern breakouts that align with VWAP direction have institutional backing — the most important confirmation you can have for intraday trades.',
'Indicator Guides', 'Pattern Confirmation', 'article', 'intermediate', 'published', 10,
