-- 8. Trend Following
('trend-following-pattern-alignment',
'Trend Following: Aligning Patterns with the Dominant Trend',
'Learn why trading patterns in the direction of the dominant trend dramatically increases win rates.',
E'## Why Trend Alignment Matters for Patterns\n\nA bull flag in an uptrend has a ~67% success rate. The same flag pattern against the trend? Closer to 40%. **Trend alignment is the single biggest factor in pattern success rates.**\n\n## How to Identify the Dominant Trend\n\n### Moving Average Stack\n- **Strong Uptrend:** 20 EMA > 50 EMA > 200 EMA, all sloping up\n- **Strong Downtrend:** 20 EMA < 50 EMA < 200 EMA, all sloping down\n- **No Trend:** MAs are flat and intertwined — avoid pattern trading\n\n### ADX (Average Directional Index)\n- **ADX > 25:** Trending market — trade continuation patterns\n- **ADX < 20:** Ranging market — trade reversal patterns at boundaries\n- **ADX rising:** Trend strengthening — look for flags and pennants\n\n### Higher Timeframe Context\n- Trade patterns on the daily chart in the direction of the weekly trend\n- Trade patterns on the 4H chart in the direction of the daily trend\n- Opposing patterns = counter-trend = lower probability\n\n## Pattern Selection by Trend Context\n\n### Strong Trend (ADX > 30)\nFocus on continuation patterns:\n- Bull/Bear Flags\n- Pennants\n- Ascending/Descending Triangles\n- Cup & Handle\n\n### Weakening Trend (ADX declining)\nWatch for reversal patterns:\n- Double Tops/Bottoms\n- Head & Shoulders\n- Wedges (contrary to trend direction)\n- Triple Tops/Bottoms\n\n### No Trend (ADX < 20)\nTrade range-bound patterns:\n- Double Tops at range resistance\n- Double Bottoms at range support\n- Wait for trend to develop\n\n## The Turtle Method for Pattern Traders\n\nRichard Dennis''s rules apply perfectly to pattern trading:\n\n1. **Let winners run:** When a pattern breakout starts trending, use trailing stops\n2. **Cut losses short:** If a pattern fails, exit immediately\n3. **Trade multiple markets:** Scan across stocks, crypto, forex for patterns\n4. **Systematic execution:** Follow detection engine signals, remove emotion\n\n## Risk Management\n\n- **With-trend patterns:** Risk 1-2% per trade\n- **Counter-trend patterns:** Risk 0.5-1% per trade (higher failure rate)\n- **Stop Loss:** 2x ATR trailing stop for trend continuation patterns\n- **Max Exposure:** 10-25% portfolio heat across all positions\n\n## Common Mistakes\n\n- Trading bullish patterns in a downtrend (hope trading)\n- Ignoring the weekly trend when trading daily patterns\n- Abandoning the strategy during normal trend pullbacks\n- Over-optimizing entry/exit parameters on historical data\n- Trading too few markets (missing trends that pay for losers)\n\n## Key Takeaway\n\nAlways ask: "Is this pattern WITH or AGAINST the trend?" With-trend patterns are your bread and butter. Counter-trend patterns are occasional opportunities that require reduced position sizes.',
'Indicator Guides', 'Pattern Confirmation', 'article', 'intermediate', 'published', 18,
